sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_074_CSMS
    Note over CP,CS: Update Charge Point Certificate by request of Central System
    Note over CP,CS: Prerequisite: Central System supports security profile 3

    CS->>CP: 1. ExtendedTriggerMessage.req
    Note right of CS: requestedMessage = SignChargePointCertificate<br/>connectorId = <Omitted>

    CP-->>CS: 2. ExtendedTriggerMessage.conf
    Note left of CP: status = Accepted

    Note over CP: Charge Point generates new<br/>public/private key pair and CSR

    CP->>CS: 3. SignCertificate.req

    CS-->>CP: 4. SignCertificate.conf
    Note right of CS: status = Accepted

    Note over CS: Certificate Authority signs the certificate

    CS->>CP: 5. CertificateSigned.req
    Note right of CS: certificateChain = signed certificate<br/>(valid PEM, matching public key,<br/>correct algorithm, CN = serialNumber)

    Note over CP: Charge Point verifies the signed certificate

    CP-->>CS: 6. CertificateSigned.conf
    Note left of CP: status = Accepted

    Note over CP: 7. Charge Point disconnects and reconnects<br/>with the new certificate

    CP->>CS: Reconnect with new certificate
    CS-->>CP: 8. Central System accepts connection
